.TH "rcu_user_enter" 9 "rcu_user_enter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rcu_user_enter \- inform RCU that we are resuming userspace.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "noinstr void" rcu_user_enter
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Enter RCU idle mode right before resuming userspace.  No use of RCU
is permitted between this call and \fBrcu_user_exit\fP. This way the
CPU doesn't need to maintain the tick for RCU maintenance purposes
when the CPU runs in userspace.

If you add or remove a call to \fBrcu_user_enter\fP, be sure to test with
CONFIG_RCU_EQS_DEBUG=y.
